snippet.textDisplay:
@Milo is life For example:
Prions & pathogenic Tau:
Copy and paste what is in quotes... (because YT blocks my comment, if I add links)

"SARS-CoV-2 spike protein interactions with amyloidogenic proteins: Potential clues to neurodegeneration"

"SARS-CoV-2 Prion-like Domains in Spike Proteins Enables Higher Affinity to ACE2"

"Highly efficient intercellular spreading of protein misfolding mediated by viral ligand-receptor interactions"

" SARS-CoV-2 nucleocapsid protein forms condensates with viral genomic RNA"

"Viral proteins help shuttle Tau aggregates among cells"

...and a general but very good paper on Prions in general... (not about or limited to SARS-CoV-2)
"There is no safe dose of Prions"

I also just found this article, which explains it quite easily what a Prion (actually a cell surface protein, but here with a wrong "charge" and hence folded wrong) ) is and how it causes a "Prion-cascade" (misfolding of normal "folded" Prions).
"Do Vampire-Like Proteins Make Coronavirus More Contagious?"
